article.headline: Valparaiso 63, IPFW 47
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. -- Kevin Van Wijk had 16 points and four blocked shots Saturday to lead Valparaiso to a 63-47 victory over IPFW. Brandon Wood added 12 points for the Crusaders (7-4) and Cory Johnson had 11. Jeremy Mixon had 14 points and Brandon Gaines 12 for IPFW (7-3), which had its six-game winning streak snapped. Wood scored the first four points of the game for Valparaiso, which never trailed and closed the half on a 13-1 run to go up 39-21 at the intermission. The Crusaders, who shot 47 percent from the field, led by as many as 26 in the second half. IPFW shot just 26 percent, including 3 of 14 on 3-point attempts.
